signal_description: The SIGNAL query is performing an operation on the table named 'defaultview-59'. It is calculating a percentage value by subtracting a certain ratio from 100. The ratio is calculated by dividing the count of 'case_id' where a subquery returns true by the total count of 'case_id'. The subquery checks if there is any 'event_name' that occurs more than once by using the 'BOOL_OR' function on the 'occurrence' column, which is the count of occurrences of 'event_name'. If there is at least one 'event_name' that occurs more than once, the subquery will return true. The result of this query will be 100 minus the percentage of 'case_id' that have at least one 'event_name' occurring more than once.

SIGNAL query: 

SELECT
100 - (COUNT(case_id) FILTER (WHERE
	(SELECT BOOL_OR (occurrence > 1)
		FROM (SELECT OCCURRENCE(event_name) AS occurrence) AS sub
)
)/COUNT(case_id)*100)
FROM "defaultview-59"
